<subSubSection box="[151,880,292,314]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,880,292,314]" box="[151,880,292,314]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">
Type species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1787" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1787" box="[294,635,292,314]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Dytiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cicurius">
<emphasis box="[294,469,293,314]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Dytiscus cicurius</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1787
</taxonomicName>
, by present designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="93" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,358,671]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,358,383]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Large (
<quantity box="[363,490,358,383]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15–16 mm</quantity>
), slender, torpedo shaped species. Labrum with medial deep emargination. Sides of pronotum distinctly bordered except for anterior angles; posterior pronotal angles weakly obtuse. Elytral surface sculpture double, consisting of moderately large polygonal meshes filled with fine polygonal cells. Setae on parameres distally acute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,358,671]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,303,502,527]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Position.</emphasis>
Sister group of the European (east-Mediterranean) genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Seidlitz, 1887" authorityName="Seidlitz" authorityYear="1887" box="[962,1273,502,527]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Melanodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[962,1105,502,526]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Melanodytes</emphasis>
Seidlitz, 1887
</taxonomicName>
, with the only species 
<taxonomicName authority="Rossi, 1792" authorityName="Rossi" authorityYear="1792" box="[239,549,538,563]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Melanodytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulatus">
<emphasis box="[239,391,539,563]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">M. pustulatus</emphasis>
(Rossi, 1792)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Moriniere" box="[608,848,538,563]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93" refString="Moriniere, J., Van Dam, M. H., Hawlitschek, O., Bergsten, J., Michat, M. C., Hendrich, L., Ribera, I., Toussaint, E. F. A. &amp; Balke, M. (2016) Phylogenetic niche conservatism explains an inverse latitudinal diversity gradient in freshwater arthropods. Scientific Reports, 6, 26340." type="journal article" year="2016">
Morinière 
<emphasis box="[727,783,539,563]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[871,936,538,563]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1832,1854]" captionTargetBox="[341,1289,339,1800]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[327,1304,339,1817]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogenetic reconstruction of Colymbetinae relationships using different methods of phylogenetic inference (Bayesian, Maximum Likelihood, Parsimony, figure modified from Morinière et al. 2016 which contains more details on analytical procedures); node support for major backbone nodes indicated with asterisks: black meaning strong support, lighter shades of grey referring to increasingly weaker support. Distribution is coded in colour and ancestral areas were inferred using the software package BioGeoBEARS (details in Morinière et al. 2016). Notes: &quot; R. signatus JFern. &quot; refers to a specimen from Juan Fernandez Archipelago (originally described as R. kuscheli Guignot, 1952)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569187/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="93" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,358,671]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,575,599]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Etymology.</emphasis>
Composed from 
<collectingRegion box="[544,603,575,598]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis box="[544,603,575,598]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Cape</emphasis>
</collectingRegion>
, region in southernmost Africa, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1047,1139,574,598]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Rhantus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1047,1139,574,598]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Rhantus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, genus of 
<taxonomicName box="[1271,1432,574,599]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Colymbetinae">Colymbetinae</taxonomicName>
; gender masculine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,358,671]" box="[199,1399,646,671]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1493295307" box="[199,1399,646,671]" country="South Africa" location="Western Cape" pageId="2" pageNumber="93" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Western Cape">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,445,646,671]" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Species composition.</emphasis>
Monotypic genus endemic to the Eastern and 
<collectingRegion box="[964,1119,647,671]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">
<collectingRegion box="[964,1055,647,670]" country="Solomon Islands" name="Western" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">Western</collectingRegion>
Cape
</collectingRegion>
regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[1247,1395,646,671]" name="South Africa" pageId="2" pageNumber="93">South Africa</collectingCountry>
:
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
